1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:02,710
(Episode 131)

2
00:00:02,810 --> 00:00:04,140
Come in.

3
00:00:04,140 --> 00:00:06,240
Look. My safe...

4
00:00:28,230 --> 00:00:30,300
What is this? CEO Chae.

5
00:00:30,870 --> 00:00:31,970
Are you kidding us?

6
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,740
This is ridiculous. Let's go.

7
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:36,470
Sir...

8
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:40,280
This can't be happening.

9
00:00:40,850 --> 00:00:42,810
My trees, my stones...

10
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:44,620
Where did they go?

11
00:00:44,620 --> 00:00:45,820
My money...

12
00:00:45,850 --> 00:00:47,190
Where did all my money go?

13
00:00:47,620 --> 00:00:50,360
Where did it go? This can't be happening.

14
00:00:52,390 --> 00:00:56,390
Where did it go?

15
00:00:57,630 --> 00:00:59,630
- Chae Hwa Young.
- Where did it go? Where is it?

16
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,700
- Your kingdom ends here.
- Where did it go? Where did it go?

17
00:01:02,770 --> 00:01:03,900
You're finished.

18
00:01:08,570 --> 00:01:10,410
I think I can get the password,

19
00:01:10,810 --> 00:01:12,440
but how do we get past the key lock?

20
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:14,850
Leave that to me.

21
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:18,720
I think I can open the lock.

22
00:01:24,090 --> 00:01:25,690
Facilities management?

23
00:01:25,690 --> 00:01:27,590
This is General Manager Ma Seo Rin.

24
00:01:27,690 --> 00:01:31,260
- Are you on the night shift?
- Yes, ma'am. How can I help you?

25
00:01:31,330 --> 00:01:34,730
For a fire safety inspection,
I need all the master keys for the annex.

26
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:35,800
Bring them to me right now.

27
00:01:35,870 --> 00:01:39,870
What? That area is
under CEO Chae's direct supervision,

28
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:42,210
so we need her approval.

29
00:01:42,210 --> 00:01:44,110
Don't you know CEO Chae is swamped...

30
00:01:44,110 --> 00:01:45,710
preparing for
the general shareholders' meeting?

31
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:49,610
Don't bother her with trivial reports
and get on her bad side.

32
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:52,850
Just bring them to me now.
I'll talk to CEO Chae myself.

33
00:01:54,490 --> 00:01:56,250
Don't you know who I am?

34
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:58,460
I'm CEO Chae's daughter.

35
00:02:00,290 --> 00:02:02,260
Yes, I'll send them up right away.

36
00:02:06,870 --> 00:02:07,870
See?

37
00:02:08,270 --> 00:02:10,740
There isn't a door in this hotel
that I can't open.

38
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:13,510
I'm impressed.
So this is why having power is so great.

39
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:18,540
- I guess so.
- But the problem is...

40
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:21,250
how to move
all those bonsai trees so quickly.

41
00:02:21,410 --> 00:02:25,120
We'll have to work with Tae Pyung
and Tae Sook to get it done.

42
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:44,940
This is the Millennium Tree
and the Fire Dragon Stone.

43
00:02:45,070 --> 00:02:48,310
Yes.
We've moved almost everything on the list.

44
00:02:50,210 --> 00:02:51,310
Hey, Tae Pyung.

45
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:53,040
Look, it doesn't matter
if the stones are on the bottom,

46
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,410
but you have to be careful
with the trees on top.

47
00:02:54,410 --> 00:02:57,150
If the cart shakes hard going over a bump,
the branches will break.

48
00:02:57,150 --> 00:03:00,050
Don't worry. I put down soft padding,
so they'll be fine.

49
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:05,120
I'm done too. We just have to load
them on the truck now, right?

50
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:06,360
- Yes.
- Yes.

51
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:10,130
Thanks, everyone.
I'll treat you all to a meal later.

52
00:03:10,260 --> 00:03:11,260
Okay.

53
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:16,670
Chae Hwa Young treasured these
like jewels,

54
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:19,200
but in the end, they're being hauled away
in a laundry cart.

55
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,310
Just like Chae Hwa Young's own fate.

56
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:22,840
That's just how power is.

57
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,340
Once it loses its master,
it's just a burden.

58
00:03:26,610 --> 00:03:29,280
Now, we just have to move the golden pine.

59
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,860
I've set up a CCTV camera over there.

60
00:03:41,090 --> 00:03:42,860
You'll be able to watch
Chae Hwa Young's downfall...

61
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:44,330
on a tablet or laptop.

62
00:03:44,430 --> 00:03:46,530
What kind of face do you think
Chae Hwa Young will make...

63
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:48,030
when she sees her golden safe is gone?

64
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:51,340
- She'll probably faint.
- It's going to be a real sight to see.

65
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:58,580
Where did it go?

66
00:03:59,380 --> 00:04:01,180
How could this happen after I worked
so hard to collect all this?

67
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:04,150
Where did it go? Where is it?

68
00:04:05,550 --> 00:04:07,390
Darn it. What on earth happened here?

69
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:09,420
CEO Chae.

70
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:11,060
This is Oh Jang Mi's doing.

71
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:13,360
Kang Baek Ho and Oh Jang Mi...

72
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,830
Those two bastards did this.
I'm sure of it.

73
00:04:15,890 --> 00:04:18,700
But how did they know about this place
to rob it?

74
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:21,630
How dare those bastards
steal all my treasures?

75
00:04:22,230 --> 00:04:24,570
Lee Kang Hyuk,
you don't know anything about this?

76
00:04:25,770 --> 00:04:28,510
How did they find out about
my golden safe?

77
00:04:28,570 --> 00:04:30,340
I'm going crazy.

78
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,290
So it was then.

79
00:04:47,530 --> 00:04:48,590
Kang Baek Ho.

80
00:04:49,130 --> 00:04:51,030
So you're going to screw me over
to the very end, is that it?

81
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:53,630
What do I do? My money...

82
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,770
The lobbying and everything...

83
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:02,740
It's all over. My hard-earned
money is gone. I'm ruined.

84
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:04,540
- Ma'am.
- CEO Chae.

85
00:05:08,410 --> 00:05:09,650
My money...

86
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:12,520
What am I going to do?

87
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:19,990
What do I do?

88
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:24,060
What do I do?

89
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:28,770
What am I going to do about all of this?
What do I do now?

90
00:05:30,070 --> 00:05:31,970
Can't you check the CCTV in the hallway?

91
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:34,640
Actually, we were trying
to strengthen security,

92
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:36,540
so the CCTV was under construction
for replacement,

93
00:05:36,610 --> 00:05:37,610
and they took advantage of that...

94
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:42,280
You're taking responsibility for this.

95
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,520
Why did you make a big deal
about changing the CCTV...

96
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:46,520
and cause this huge disaster?

97
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:50,660
What are you going to do about my money?
My hard-earned money!

98
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:53,490
Calm down. Panicking won't solve anything.

99
00:05:54,630 --> 00:05:56,890
You should have been monitoring it
around the clock.

100
00:05:57,330 --> 00:06:01,130
How could you be so negligent
with security?

101
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:02,900
What are you going to do?

102
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:04,670
What are you going to do about my money?

103
00:06:05,170 --> 00:06:06,440
I'm sorry.

104
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:09,810
I'll find the culprit no matter what
and get it all back.

105
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,880
And how will you do that?

106
00:06:12,310 --> 00:06:13,850
It's obvious Oh Jang Mi did this.

107
00:06:14,450 --> 00:06:15,580
Find them now.

108
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:17,880
Search all the CCTV footage
from the Disaster Control Room.

109
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:20,990
And check all the parking lot CCTV
to find a clue.

110
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:23,990
Otherwise, Lee Kang Hyuk,
you will take full responsibility.

111
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:38,640
To think each of these is worth
hundreds of thousands dollars.

112
00:06:39,370 --> 00:06:42,240
Jang Mi,
let's just quietly cash these in...

113
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:43,740
and use it as seed money for our business.

114
00:06:43,810 --> 00:06:46,410
No way. This is clearly stolen property.

115
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,010
The moment we cash it,

116
00:06:48,010 --> 00:06:49,950
we'll all end up in handcuffs...

117
00:06:50,010 --> 00:06:51,820
for money laundering and possession
of stolen goods.

118
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:54,790
Chae Hwa Young has probably realized
that we took these.

119
00:06:55,220 --> 00:06:57,260
It's obvious she's just waiting
for the right moment.

120
00:06:57,790 --> 00:07:00,220
She's waiting for us to use this
for our own selfish gain,

121
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,290
then she'll report us.

122
00:07:02,490 --> 00:07:06,500
- Oh, right.
- So it's a problem to keep and return it.

123
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,800
The way to take it from her
that will hurt the most is...

124
00:07:09,970 --> 00:07:13,100
to send it somewhere
the owner can never get it back from.

125
00:07:13,570 --> 00:07:15,270
We'll let the whole world know...

126
00:07:15,340 --> 00:07:18,310
so that Chae Hwa Young
can't claim they're hers.

127
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:21,680
The most perfect way to dispose of it
is to return it for the public's benefit.

128
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:22,810
What does that mean?

129
00:07:24,350 --> 00:07:28,350
- Give it to the government?
- No, to the warmest place.

130
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:30,250
We donate it to an orphanage.

131
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:33,320
You want to send these expensive trees
to a place with kids?

132
00:07:34,590 --> 00:07:37,060
Yes. An orphanage is a great idea.

133
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:39,860
It's good
for the kids' emotional well-being,

134
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:43,130
and more importantly, it's a place
that gets a lot of public attention.

135
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:45,440
Artistic bonsai worth
hundreds of millions of dollars...

136
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,170
donated by an anonymous philanthropist.

137
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:50,940
If it makes the news,
Chae Hwa Young will be robbed blind.

138
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:54,410
That's right. She won't be able to
say a peep about wanting them back.

139
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:57,250
Exactly. If she tries to claim ownership,

140
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:59,380
it'd be like confessing
to her own slush fund,

141
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:00,650
so she'll never be able to report it.

142
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:03,250
Then, Chae Hwa Young is going
to cry tears of blood.

143
00:08:03,690 --> 00:08:04,690
Serves her right.

144
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:09,090
Turning Chae Hwa Young's dirty money
into green trees for children.

145
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:12,300
This will make for a pretty unique ending.

146
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:16,070
Let's go now with all the bonsai trees
loaded on the truck.

147
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,740
It will be a gift for the kids.

148
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:19,140
Let's do it!

149
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:21,370
- Let's do it!
- Let's do it!

150
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:23,610
Hey, be careful.

151
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:33,020
Darn it, I'm screwed.

152
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,720
I can't believe Oh Jang Mi
got out of prison so quickly.

153
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,320
Mom.

154
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:40,060
What did the doctor say?

155
00:08:40,590 --> 00:08:43,090
Is there any chance
the Chairman will wake up?

156
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:45,800
It's not a matter of chance.
He absolutely must wake up...

157
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:49,600
so he can make sure I get my share.

158
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,940
I can't let them kick me
out of the house empty-handed.

159
00:08:55,110 --> 00:08:58,440
I've got insurance on Chae Hwa Young.

160
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:59,480
What?

161
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:00,750
What insurance?

162
00:09:01,410 --> 00:09:02,480
It's just something I have.

163
00:09:04,650 --> 00:09:07,550
I kept some evidence with this.

164
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,720
I'll...

165
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:12,360
use it if I have to.

166
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,890
Do you not know what a vicious snake
Chae Hwa Young is?

167
00:09:15,260 --> 00:09:17,500
Don't you dare say a word.

168
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:20,360
What if the Chairman really passes away?
What will we do?

169
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,900
We have to get something
out of this situation, don't we?

170
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:22,970
I don't know, darn it.

171
00:09:23,570 --> 00:09:24,670
You're giving me a headache.

172
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:36,950
Thank you for staying this long.
Go get some rest now.

173
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:40,150
What took you so long?
I'm starving to death.

174
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,360
Father.

175
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:55,030
Jang Mi and Baek Ho...

176
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:58,940
are fighting so hard
to protect Dream Group.

177
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,040
So please, Father,

178
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,510
wake up soon.

179
00:10:03,510 --> 00:10:04,610
Please?

180
00:10:06,980 --> 00:10:08,050
If...

181
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:09,280
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

182
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:11,280
we can't get the bonsai trees back,

183
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:15,650
we have to give up on all our dreams.

184
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:17,520
With your abilities,

185
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:20,420
you can definitely become the chairman.

186
00:10:22,460 --> 00:10:26,160
Everyone who helped me was on my payroll.

187
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:30,800
Do you really think
Oh Jang Mi and Kang Baek Ho...

188
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,440
haven't been gathering evidence
against me this whole time?

189
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,710
Still, it's too soon to be disappointed.

190
00:10:34,970 --> 00:10:35,970
No.

191
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,540
I've been using my money
to keep them quiet,

192
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:40,810
but that's impossible
without enough money.

193
00:10:41,510 --> 00:10:44,550
The ever-tenacious Chairman Ma didn't die,

194
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,520
and my dream of becoming
the chairman of Dream...

195
00:10:49,090 --> 00:10:50,590
has become a long shot.

196
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,640
An anonymous philanthropist
has donated bonsai trees...

197
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,870
worth tens, or possibly hundreds,
of millions of dollars...

198
00:11:06,870 --> 00:11:09,770
to the Hope Orphanage,
and it's making headlines.

199
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:12,810
What an amazing person.

200
00:11:13,110 --> 00:11:17,620
To just donate such rare
and expensive bonsai for kids to enjoy.

201
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:20,650
Now that it's been confirmed their value
and scale are beyond imagination,

202
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:22,320
it's becoming a huge story.

203
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:24,790
Yes, I'm here now
in the front yard of Hope Orphanage.

204
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:26,560
- What?
- Do you see...

205
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:28,030
- My bonsai trees...
- the bonsai trees behind me?

206
00:11:28,490 --> 00:11:29,660
These are the premium bonsai...

207
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:32,500
an anonymous philanthropist donated
to this orphanage last night.

208
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,570
According to expert appraisers,

209
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:37,940
this pine and juniper are worth
millions of dollars...

210
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,770
and have been identified
as premium bonsai,

211
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,710
- shocking the public.
- No.

212
00:11:42,110 --> 00:11:44,710
I can't give my gold
to those snot-nosed brats.

213
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:47,310
They're mine. It's my gold.

214
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:50,880
When I came in this morning,
I found a letter.

215
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:53,750
It came with a message,
hoping they'd be used...

216
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:55,320
for the children's emotional enrichment.

217
00:11:55,920 --> 00:12:00,420
And the donor was simply signed,
"Your animal friends."

218
00:12:00,890 --> 00:12:04,360
I'd like to express my deepest gratitude
to them.

219
00:12:11,070 --> 00:12:13,770
I bet Chae Hwa Young
is crying her eyes out right now.

220
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:17,480
With this, I think we've completely
wiped out Chae Hwa Young's slush fund.

221
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:20,340
Now that her dream of taking over Dream
has been crushed,

222
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:22,350
she must be absolutely losing her mind.

223
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:25,550
Manager Lee, gather your men right now...

224
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:28,190
and storm the orphanage.
Bring me back all of my bonsai trees.

225
00:12:28,450 --> 00:12:30,220
It's my money.
It's my blood, sweat, and tears.

226
00:12:30,290 --> 00:12:33,420
- You can't do that.
- Why not?

227
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:36,560
If you all won't go, then I'll go myself
and get it all back.

228
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:38,760
And what will you say when you get there?

229
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:40,030
Are you going to announce on a bullhorn...

230
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:42,230
that those multi-million-dollar
bonsai trees are your slush fund?

231
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,540
Well...

232
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:48,340
It was on national television.

233
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:50,570
The moment you show up
demanding them back,

234
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:54,510
it would be the same as you confessing
to hiding a huge slush fund warehouse.

235
00:12:54,810 --> 00:12:57,520
So this is what Kang Baek Ho
and Oh Jang Mi were after.

236
00:12:58,220 --> 00:12:59,550
A perfect checkmate.

237
00:13:01,090 --> 00:13:02,090
My money.

238
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:04,320
My slush fund.

239
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:16,270
Wait, all those bonsai trees
are Hwa Young's slush fund?

240
00:13:33,050 --> 00:13:34,250
Jun Ho, that boy.

241
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:37,150
Without saying a single word
about leaving,

242
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:41,030
he packed up all his clothes and left.

243
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:45,760
How could he do this?

244
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:49,170
It's as if I'm not even his mother.

245
00:13:52,170 --> 00:13:54,510
I know blood is thicker than water,
but still...

246
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:58,210
How could he do this to me?

247
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:05,880
Can't you just tell me the truth?

248
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:07,020
(General Manager Ma Seo Rin)

249
00:14:07,020 --> 00:14:08,890
The day Grandfather collapsed,

250
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:11,690
don't you remember telling me to go home?

251
00:14:15,290 --> 00:14:16,690
General Manager Ma.

252
00:14:18,330 --> 00:14:22,170
My mom had to go out,
and she called on her way.

253
00:14:22,530 --> 00:14:25,070
She asked me to stay with the Chairman
since he's home alone.

254
00:14:26,170 --> 00:14:27,170
Really?

255
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:30,140
Why do you ask?

256
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:34,110
My mom called me,
and I was just relaying her message.

257
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:37,780
Don't lie.
You're saying your mother called you?

258
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:40,520
Of course. Why would I lie?

259
00:14:40,620 --> 00:14:43,120
You conspired with Chae Hwa Young
to set a trap for me.

260
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:44,890
Did you think I wouldn't find out?

261
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:51,530
San Wol, I just have one question for you.

262
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,970
On the day Grandfather collapsed,
what time did you leave?

263
00:14:55,230 --> 00:14:56,370
What time?

264
00:14:56,370 --> 00:14:57,740
I left at ten.

265
00:14:58,240 --> 00:15:00,940
Why? I went to the salon
to get my hair done...

266
00:15:00,940 --> 00:15:01,970
and then to see a musical.

267
00:15:02,110 --> 00:15:04,910
Then you must have also called Hong Ju
before the musical.

268
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:08,050
No, why would I call Hong Ju?

269
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:10,080
I was in a rush to get to the musical.

270
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:12,320
But why? Why are you asking?

271
00:15:13,380 --> 00:15:16,120
Are you suspecting me of being involved
in the Chairman’s collapse?

272
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:19,020
(General Manager Ma Seo Rin)

273
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:20,760
Well?

274
00:15:21,660 --> 00:15:23,130
You'd better confess now.

275
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:25,730
If you don't tell me the whole truth,

276
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:28,300
I'll report you
as Chae Hwa Young's accomplice.

277
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:36,110
I'm not trying to accuse you
of a crime right now.

278
00:15:37,310 --> 00:15:39,980
If you repent
and apologize to Grandfather...

279
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:43,210
and reveal your conspiracy
with Chae Hwa Young,

280
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:46,920
I'll resolve this
without getting the police involved.

281
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:55,630
I was going to let it slide
since we live under the same roof.

282
00:15:56,690 --> 00:15:57,700
But I see that's not going to work.

283
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:01,870
From now on, I'll treat you
as one of Chae Hwa Young's people.

284
00:16:02,470 --> 00:16:04,000
I warned you.

285
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:08,510
Wait.

286
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:11,440
Give me some time.

287
00:16:19,420 --> 00:16:20,420
Hwa Young.

288
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:24,960
No matter how upset you are,
one sip of this will calm you down.

289
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:27,760
She's not in the mood for tea right now.
Take it away.

290
00:16:28,990 --> 00:16:30,660
We'll figure out a solution,

291
00:16:30,660 --> 00:16:32,630
so please don't worry yourself sick,
ma'am.

292
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:49,350
Hey, look at them. Isn't that ridiculous?

293
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:51,920
Look at Chae Hwa Young,
what a pathetic sight.

294
00:16:52,050 --> 00:16:54,050
With her Blue Dragon on the left
and White Tiger on the right,

295
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:55,550
what does she think she's doing?

296
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:57,960
- Goodness.
- Mom.

297
00:16:58,990 --> 00:17:00,960
But is something wrong with you?

298
00:17:01,130 --> 00:17:03,560
Mom, why did you say unnecessary things
and make things difficult for me?

299
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:06,660
- What?
- When you talked to Oh Jang Mi,

300
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:10,100
why did you say you never called me?

301
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:11,370
Because of you,

302
00:17:11,370 --> 00:17:14,470
I'm about to get caught for playing
a part in the Chairman collapsing.

303
00:17:14,770 --> 00:17:18,210
I might go to jail
as CEO Chae's accomplice.

304
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,310
What are you going to do?

305
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:22,850
What? What in the world
are you talking about?

306
00:17:24,010 --> 00:17:25,180
What did you say?

307
00:17:25,180 --> 00:17:26,750
What did Oh Jang Mi say?

308
00:17:28,450 --> 00:17:32,820
Oh Jang Mi found out that I worked
with you to make the Chairman collapse.

309
00:17:32,890 --> 00:17:34,460
What did you just say you did?

310
00:17:34,730 --> 00:17:36,790
Are you out of your mind?

311
00:17:37,130 --> 00:17:38,460
Jin Hong Ju, there's no need to be scared.

312
00:17:38,830 --> 00:17:40,730
I covered up that case again, didn't I?

313
00:17:41,370 --> 00:17:43,600
Even if she knows,
there's nothing Oh Jang Mi can do.

314
00:17:43,770 --> 00:17:45,240
I don't think that's true.

315
00:17:45,370 --> 00:17:47,000
It seems Oh Jang Mi looked into it,

316
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,910
identified you and me as the culprits,

317
00:17:49,170 --> 00:17:50,770
and she's planning to go to the police.

318
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:52,010
I told you that won't happen.

319
00:17:52,810 --> 00:17:53,840
Jin Hong Ju, listen carefully.

320
00:17:54,610 --> 00:17:56,580
Oh Jang Mi wants to take me down.

321
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:59,380
She's just using a small fry like you
as bait.

322
00:17:59,750 --> 00:18:03,150
Don't get tricked and caught in her trap.
Got it?

323
00:18:04,190 --> 00:18:05,220
Lawyer Han?

324
00:18:23,870 --> 00:18:24,980
Kang Jun Ho.

325
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:27,180
How could you do this to me?

326
00:18:27,910 --> 00:18:29,610
After I raised you for 30 years,

327
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,580
is this how you repay me?

328
00:18:32,450 --> 00:18:36,990
You could have at least told me
you were leaving.

329
00:18:37,090 --> 00:18:38,390
What should I have said?

330
00:18:38,390 --> 00:18:40,390
"I'm going to find my birth mother."

331
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,960
"So you can live happily
with Kang Baek Ho, the one you adore."

332
00:18:44,390 --> 00:18:45,730
Is that what I should have said
when I left?

333
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:47,630
Jun Ho.

334
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:50,230
How could you say something like that?

335
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:51,300
Do you really think...

336
00:18:51,670 --> 00:18:55,170
I played favorites while raising you?

337
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:58,510
Stop it. What's the point of all this now?

338
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:02,210
Why do you feel so inferior to Baek Ho?

339
00:19:02,450 --> 00:19:05,620
You're brilliant in your own right.
Why can't you see that?

340
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:07,520
You think I'm brilliant?

341
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:12,290
When my mother is a murderer,
and my father is her accomplice?

342
00:19:13,020 --> 00:19:14,020
What?

343
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:19,230
That's not true.

344
00:19:20,230 --> 00:19:24,100
Your mother isn't Chae Hwa Young.
It's me, Han Young Ja.

345
00:19:25,870 --> 00:19:28,210
Stop it. What is wrong with you?

346
00:19:28,270 --> 00:19:30,470
What are you doing, causing a scene
in someone else's house?

347
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:31,540
Get out now.

348
00:19:31,610 --> 00:19:33,440
What? "Someone else's house?"

349
00:19:35,780 --> 00:19:36,880
You bastard.

350
00:19:37,610 --> 00:19:41,120
We haven't even signed
the divorce papers yet.

351
00:19:41,220 --> 00:19:43,320
Your legal wife is standing right here,
very much alive.

352
00:19:43,790 --> 00:19:44,890
Do you really have to...

353
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:48,190
live with your mistress
and my son under one roof?

354
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,930
So classless.

355
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:51,730
You may not have signed
the divorce papers,

356
00:19:51,730 --> 00:19:53,160
but aren't you two already done?

357
00:19:53,430 --> 00:19:55,100
Who do you think you are,
acting like his wife?

358
00:19:55,370 --> 00:19:57,670
Stop being so pathetic
and get out of my house.

359
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,440
What did you say?

360
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:03,270
You cold-blooded, venomous witch.

361
00:20:03,810 --> 00:20:07,810
Hey. Wasn't it enough
that you destroyed my family?

362
00:20:07,910 --> 00:20:10,150
- Now you're stealing my son?
- Hey.

363
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:13,050
Young Ja, stop it.
Do you have to be like this?

364
00:20:16,690 --> 00:20:17,990
Hey, Manager Lee.

365
00:20:17,990 --> 00:20:21,590
That went too far.
How could you treat a woman like that?

366
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:24,700
This thug is showing his true colors
everywhere he goes.

367
00:20:25,260 --> 00:20:26,260
Shut up.

368
00:20:26,730 --> 00:20:28,630
If I'm a thug,
does that make you a philanderer?

369
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:31,370
Who are you to be having an affair
and running your mouth?

370
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:33,470
What does my affair have to do with you?

371
00:20:33,470 --> 00:20:35,670
How dare you even mention
the word "affair"?

372
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:38,310
I told you! What we have is a noble love.

373
00:20:38,310 --> 00:20:39,610
Unbelievable!

374
00:20:41,010 --> 00:20:43,250
I can't stand to listen to this filth.

375
00:20:43,610 --> 00:20:47,350
Are the adulterous couple and the murderer
competing to see who's more disgusting?

376
00:20:47,420 --> 00:20:49,420
Shut up, Han Young Ja. Get out now.

377
00:20:49,420 --> 00:20:50,950
Drag that woman out of here now.

378
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:52,220
Enough!

379
00:20:55,260 --> 00:20:56,590
Please, just stop.

380
00:20:57,430 --> 00:20:58,430
Please.

381
00:21:15,910 --> 00:21:18,080
Thanks for taking me home, Kang Hyuk.

382
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:26,120
Yes, Prosecutor General.

383
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:31,500
This month's is a bit late,
but please just wait a little longer.

384
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:33,660
Yes, soon.

385
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:34,770
Sure.

386
00:21:40,070 --> 00:21:41,770
Kang Hyuk, could you bring me some water?

387
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:43,110
Sure.

388
00:21:48,180 --> 00:21:50,010
(Message)

389
00:21:51,620 --> 00:21:53,150
Two for this month.

390
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:57,820
Mom, we need to know which powerful people
are backing Chae Hwa Young.

391
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:05,060
- Here.
- Thanks.

392
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:14,600
Your mother found out
who is backing Chae Hwa Young?

393
00:22:15,010 --> 00:22:17,870
Yes,
it's not the current Prosecutor General.

394
00:22:17,940 --> 00:22:19,810
It was the one who resigned a while ago.

395
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:21,650
But he still has a lot of pull,

396
00:22:21,650 --> 00:22:23,480
so it seems Chae Hwa Young
is still benefiting.

397
00:22:23,750 --> 00:22:26,380
Then we'll have to find his weakness,

398
00:22:26,650 --> 00:22:28,590
so he can't cover for
Chae Hwa Young anymore.

399
00:22:29,090 --> 00:22:30,420
We'll have to put the screws to him.

400
00:22:31,490 --> 00:22:34,420
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

401
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:37,790
Haven't you found a buyer
to take the whole hotel yet?

402
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:41,670
Before the board meeting, we need
to sell off the building right away,

403
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:43,330
grab the cash, and get out of here.

404
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:44,940
That's the only way now.

405
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,100
Selling the entire hotel is suicide.

406
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:48,910
To sell a hotel worth billions,

407
00:22:49,070 --> 00:22:51,010
you need a special resolution
at a general shareholders' meeting.

408
00:22:51,010 --> 00:22:52,510
Even if we get lucky and sell it,

409
00:22:52,610 --> 00:22:55,280
the moment you wire those hundreds
of millions to a Swiss account,

410
00:22:55,580 --> 00:22:58,750
you'll be flagged
by the Financial Intelligence Unit.

411
00:22:59,050 --> 00:23:01,220
You'll be in handcuffs
before you even reach the airport gate.

412
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:02,520
You think I don't know that?

413
00:23:02,990 --> 00:23:05,260
It's because there are no other options.

414
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:07,120
Leave the building shell intact...

415
00:23:07,690 --> 00:23:10,090
and just sell off the prime assets inside.

416
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:11,360
Right.

417
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:13,500
The resort
and the duty-free shop contracts...

418
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,470
are Dream Hotel's core cash cows.

419
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:17,930
We can sell those off on the cheap.

420
00:23:18,170 --> 00:23:21,200
I can use my authority as CEO
to do it behind the board's back.

421
00:23:21,470 --> 00:23:23,070
We have to do it fast.

422
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:26,080
I doubt we can pull it off cleanly
in such a short amount of time.

423
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:29,250
It will be hard to find an overseas buyer
willing to take on...

424
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:32,220
such an astronomical, illicit deal.

425
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:34,280
There are ruthless corporate raiders...

426
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:38,020
who hunt only the most valuable companies.

427
00:23:39,460 --> 00:23:42,660
- They exist. Find them.
- Yes, ma'am.

428
00:23:42,990 --> 00:23:46,830
By the way, Prosecutor General Hwang
keeps calling about his payment.

429
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:50,330
Worthless leeches.
Haven't they taken enough already?

430
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,300
How can they keep pestering me
for monthly payments?

431
00:23:54,370 --> 00:23:56,710
Is there any way to get some cash?

432
00:23:58,580 --> 00:24:00,540
The company's financial situation
is not good right now.

433
00:24:02,210 --> 00:24:03,910
This is all Oh Jang Mi's fault.

434
00:24:07,020 --> 00:24:10,750
I'm sure Chae Hwa Young
is already planning her next move.

435
00:24:11,660 --> 00:24:14,360
I'm sure she is.
Her slush fund was completely wiped out,

436
00:24:14,420 --> 00:24:15,930
so she can't make her bribe payments,

437
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:19,730
which means she'll have to pay
for her crimes,

438
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:21,160
so she must be feeling very anxious.

439
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:24,170
Then she must be scrambling
to get her hands on some cash.

440
00:24:24,230 --> 00:24:26,800
She might be planning to use
raising funds as an excuse...

441
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:30,310
to sell off the hotel's most
valuable assets one by one.

442
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:37,550
It's an unknown number.

443
00:24:39,150 --> 00:24:40,520
Yes, this is Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

444
00:24:49,390 --> 00:24:50,430
Mom.

445
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:55,070
You've had such a hard time...

446
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:57,330
taking care of Grandfather
at the hospital.

447
00:24:57,970 --> 00:24:59,140
Here, try this on.

448
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:02,310
What's this?

449
00:25:03,170 --> 00:25:04,340
What’s that dress?

450
00:25:04,340 --> 00:25:07,240
I bought it
because I wanted to see you in it.

451
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:11,410
Mom, please change into this now...

452
00:25:11,750 --> 00:25:13,920
and go to the location I'm sending you.

453
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:17,190
There's someone there
who really wants to see you.

454
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:19,460
Someone wants to see me?

455
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:21,520
Who?

456
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:28,470
You'll see when you get there.

457
00:25:28,870 --> 00:25:29,870
Mom.

458
00:25:30,370 --> 00:25:31,400
All this time,

459
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,300
you've really been through so much, Mom.

460
00:25:34,770 --> 00:25:35,770
Okay.

461
00:25:42,310 --> 00:25:44,980
Is this the place Jang Mi told me to go?

462
00:25:46,520 --> 00:25:49,490
Who on earth wants to see me so badly...

463
00:25:49,750 --> 00:25:51,550
that they'd ask to meet
in a place like this?

464
00:25:52,860 --> 00:25:57,060
Could it be a friend from the orphanage?

465
00:26:00,030 --> 00:26:01,260
They must have met...

466
00:26:01,930 --> 00:26:03,470
by now, right?

467
00:26:04,970 --> 00:26:06,470
It must be a happy moment for them.

468
00:26:09,270 --> 00:26:12,440
I just wish Grandfather
would wake up soon.

469
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:15,250
Don't worry too much.

470
00:26:15,850 --> 00:26:17,480
The doctor said his prognosis is good.

471
00:26:17,750 --> 00:26:19,380
He'll shake this off
and be back on his feet.

472
00:26:38,370 --> 00:26:39,370
Excuse me.

473
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:42,740
Are you waiting for me?

474
00:26:58,190 --> 00:26:59,490
Dong Seok?

475
00:27:00,890 --> 00:27:02,130
Is it really...

476
00:27:03,460 --> 00:27:04,790
you, Dong Seok?

477
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:17,110
It's been a long time, Suk Hee.

478
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:19,910
Dong Seok.

479
00:27:21,310 --> 00:27:22,710
Is it you, Dong Seok?

480
00:27:25,150 --> 00:27:26,180
How...

481
00:27:27,350 --> 00:27:28,450
How...

482
00:27:30,490 --> 00:27:31,620
Yes, that's right.

483
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,790
It's your husband,

484
00:27:36,990 --> 00:27:38,030
Ma Dong Seok.

485
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,100
Suk Hee.

486
00:27:46,670 --> 00:27:47,770
Dong Seok.

487
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:15,300
(The First Man)

488
00:28:15,430 --> 00:28:16,700
This afternoon,
off the coast of Incheon...

489
00:28:16,770 --> 00:28:18,170
That's Kim Bum Seok from the auto shop.

490
00:28:18,230 --> 00:28:20,170
The one who tried to extort money
from Chae Hwa Young.

491
00:28:20,340 --> 00:28:22,210
Ssangkal's girlfriend is in danger too.

492
00:28:22,610 --> 00:28:25,010
If we just know
where Lee Kang Hyuk is operating,

493
00:28:25,010 --> 00:28:27,540
we might be able to figure out
what Chae Hwa Young is plotting.

494
00:28:27,780 --> 00:28:29,010
Manager Lee took the bait.

495
00:28:29,050 --> 00:28:31,750
We're tracking Manager Lee's location
in real time.

496
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:35,290
The head of a major private equity fund
that operates between Europe and Asia...

497
00:28:35,290 --> 00:28:36,920
is keeping an eye on Dream Hotel.

498
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:38,420
Martin Jang?

499
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:42,730
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
